abstract_ssm: The collection holds 22 black-and-white photographs taken by photojournalist Teun Voeten in 1994-95, and used for his 1996 publication "Tunnelmensen" (in the original Dutch) or "Tunnel People" in the English translation. These photographs document the lives of a community of people who resided at the time in the Amtrak railroad tunnels under Riverside Park in upper Manhattan.
